//JPA

/*
JPA is a set of rules that defines how Java objects map to database tables.

It does not do anything by itself , it needs a provider like Hibernate to work.

*/

//Hibernate

/*
Hibernate is an ORM tool that implements JPA, that helps us manage sessions,
transactions, and queries manually.

eg: 
Session session = sessionFactory.openSession();
Transaction tx = session.beginTransaction();
session.save(employee);
tx.commit();
session.close();

*/

//Spring_Data_JPA

/*
It is a Spring module that uses JPA and Hibernate to simplify data access.
It is combination of rules and excution 
eg:
public interface EmployeeRepository extends JpaRepository<Employee, Integer> {}

@Autowired
EmployeeRepository repo;
repo.save(employee); 
*/
